Happy 75th Birthday to the one and only Alice Cooper! We’re looking forward to hitting the road with Alice on the Freaks on Parade Tour starting in late August. 

We want to take this opportunity to call out Alice Cooper’s charity Solid Rock Teen Centers. Alice’s charity does remarkable work to encourage and support young people and offers ALL youth ages 12-20 a safe space to spend their time and free music lessons. If you have the means and want to celebrate Alice’s birthday by supporting the cause, please make a donation to their charity at AliceCooperSolidRock.com.

📢 Alternative-industrial rockers, FILTER First Headline Shows in Australia and NZ since 2000 as part of The Algorithm World Tour!

Filter’s frontman and creative mastermind, Richard Patrick has spent over 30 years pushing the boundaries of musical expression. Filter’s debut, 'Short Bus' achieved platinum status, propelled by "Hey Man Nice Shot". The follow up 'Title of Record', also went platinum thanks to "Take a Picture". This year Patrick unleashed the new Filter album ‘The Algorithm’, which has delivered a sonic revolution for fans worldwide.

Singer & songwriter, @filter_richard_patrick, of industrial rock band, @officialfilter, joins us on this episode of #TheAdamantiumPodcast.
